9. Nd2 {This is an example from My System. Nimzowitsch claims that the right
plan in such positions is to protect the e5 pawn with the pieces as much as
you can. In this case Black will be totally out of counterplay and only then
we can start an attack.} Ne7 10. Nf3 $1 Ng6 11. Re1 $1 Bb4 12. c3 Ba5 13. Bf4
$1 O-O 14. Bg3 Bc7 {Everything is ready for the attack} 15. Ng5 $1 Rfe8 16. Nf4
Nh8 17. Qg4 Nf8 18. Re3 $1 {suddenly all White's pieces are around Black's king
} b6 (18... Bd8) 19. Nh5 Nhg6 20. Rf3 Re7 {[%mdl 32768]} 21. Nf6+ Kh8 22. Nfxh7
Nxh7 23. Nxf7+ Rxf7 24. Rxf7 1-0

