1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. c3 d5 4. e5 Nc6 5. d4 Qb6 6. Bd3 Bd7 7. dxc5 Bxc5 8. O-O
f6 9. b4 $1 {We rarely take on f6, when Black can recapture with the knight}
Be7 10. b5 Nxe5 11. Nxe5 fxe5 12. Qh5+ Kd8 {From now until the end of the game,
Black will have problems with his king's safety.} 13. Qxe5 Nf6 14. Bf4 Rf8 15.
Bg3 Rc8 16. a4 g6 17. Qe2 Nh5 18. c4 {Very typical idea for this structure,
White opens the center} Nxg3 19. hxg3 dxc4 20. Bxc4 Qd4 21. Nd2 {The engine
will probably defend such a position, but this is almost impossible for humans.
White won very quickly after.} Bb4 22. Bd3 Rc3 23. Be4 b6 24. Rad1 $18 Qf6 25.
Bc6 Rf7 26. Ne4 Qe5 27. Nxc3 Bxc3 28. Qxe5 Bxe5 29. Rfe1 1-0

