{Playing on both flangs} 11. b3 $5 {Very clever plan. White already has a
space advantage on the kingside and now he opens a second front of the attack.
For some reason, this logical plan wasn't used before. Regardless of what
happens next, it's useful for white to open the b-file. 2 wings strategy!} Nb6
12. bxc4 bxc4 (12... Nxc4 $5 13. Nxc4 bxc4 14. Rb1 $18) 13. a4 $5 {[%csl Rb6,
Rc6] Taking care of the queenside before launching an attack on the other
flank.} Bd7 14. Nf1 Ra7 (14... Qc7) 15. Ng3 h5 {Black is trying to block the
queenside} 16. h4 $5 {[%cal Gf3g5,Gd1f3]} Bxh4 {Black accept the challenge and
take the pawn.} 17. Nxh4 Qxh4 18. Be3 Qd8 (18... Rb7 19. Rb1 Rb8 20. Qc1 Qd8
21. Bg5 Qc7 22. Bh4 $16 {[%cal Gc1g5,Ge1e3,Ge3f3]}) 19. Nxh5 Qh4 20. g4 $16 {
It's clear that Black is in trouble because there is nothing he can do to
oppose White's play on the kingside.} Qh3 {[%csl Gf3]} 21. Rb1 $5 {[%csl Gb1]}
(21. Nxg7+ $5 Kd8 22. Nh5 Rg8 23. g5 Rh8 24. Ng3 Ne7 25. Qf3 $16) (21. Bg5 Qxc3
22. Nxg7+ Kf8 23. Nh5 $1 $18) 21... Nc8 22. Bd2 $5 {[%cal Ge1e3]} g6 23. Re3
Qh4 24. Nf6+ Kd8 25. Qf3 Qh2+ 26. Kf1 $18 {and White soon win the game.} 1-0

