1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nf3 Nh6 6. Bd3 cxd4 7. Bxh6 {Very
often the move Bxh6 is a common theme in Advanced French. White ruins Black's
kingside structure and also exchange for his potentially bad bishop.} gxh6 8.
cxd4 Bd7 9. Nc3 Qb6 {Black hopes were connected with this move, but White has
a strong reply at his disposal.} 10. Bb5 $1 Rg8 (10... Bg7 {keeping the option
to castle short seems more logical.}) 11. O-O Nxe5 $4 {Bareev went for
complications, but this simply doesn't work and now White is winning almost by
force after:} ({better was} 11... O-O-O {but White keeps the advantage after:}
12. Qd3 $16 {[%cal Ra2a3,Rb2b4]}) 12. Nxe5 Bxb5 13. Qh5 Rg7 14. Rfe1 Rd8 15.
Nxb5 Qxb5 16. Nxf7 $1 {the final blow} Rxf7 17. Rxe6+ 1-0

