Baden 2019}) 8... Bd7 9. b4 cxb3 10. Nxb3 $1 {This was completely new for me
and only after this game I check the database and see a few other examples. I
am not claiming that White has an advantage in this line, but at least the
position is quite playable.} (10. c4 {was an old theory which doesn't work
very well for White}) 10... Ba4 11. Nxa5 Bxd1 (11... Qxa5 {Not accepting the
sacrifice is not an option. White enjoys easy game after:} 12. Qd2 Bc6 13. Bd3
Ne7 14. O-O {[%cal Rf3e1,Rf2f4,Rf4f5,Rd2f4,Rf3g5] 1-0 (45) Tokhirjonova,G 
(2350)-Socko,M (2421) Chess.com INT 2021}) 12. Rxb6 axb6 13. Bb5+ Ke7 (13...
Kd8 14. Nxb7+ Kc7 15. Nd6 Bxf3 16. Nxf7 Bxg2 17. Rg1 Be4 18. Nxh8 $14 {1-0 (29)
Shirov,A (2662)-Sumaneev,D (2450) Chess.com INT 2021}) 14. Kxd1 bxa5 (14...
Rxa5 15. a4 {we get a similar position like in the game but with double pawns
on the b-file and a passive rook on a5.} f6 16. Re1 Rxb5 17. axb5 $14 {1-0 (50)
Jones,G (2665)-Haria,R (2490) London 2021}) 15. a4 {The smoke is gone and we
