Bd7 Ke7 26. Bb5 {White still has the initiative, but Duda manages to defend
this unpleasant position and the game ends in a draw.} Kd8 27. f4 Ne7 28. Ke3
h4 29. h3 Nf5+ 30. Nxf5 Rxf5 31. Rg7 Rh8 32. Rxb7 Rhf8 33. Rd7+ Kc8 34. Kd4
